{"article_id":"JyqAuSE4q0ADW3ZV","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The White House on Sunday said","depth":8},{"id":1,"text":"that it is working on new guidelines for health care workers","depth":9},{"id":2,"text":"returning from Ebola-stricken areas ,","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"according to a senior administration official .","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"The decision comes","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"as governors in Illinois , New Jersey and New York announced over the weekend","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"that they were instituting quarantines for aid workers","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"returning from Ebola-stricken West Africa .","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"The White House stopped short of calling on the governors to reverse their quarantine rules ,","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"but administration officials have made clear to the governors","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"that they have concerns with unintended consequences of polices","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"not grounded in science ,","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"said a senior administration official ,","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"who asked not to be identified","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"to discuss the private communications .","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"The new guidelines are expected to be unveiled in the coming days ,","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"the official said.","depth":6},{"id":17,"text":"The official added","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"that the administration is consulting with the states","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"as they develop the new rules .","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"Earlier , other aides to President Obama criticized the decisions by three states","depth":6},{"id":21,"text":"to quarantine people","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"who are returning from Ebola-stricken West Africa .","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"Anthony Fauci , director of the National Institute of Allergy and Infectious Diseases , and United Nations Ambassador Samantha Power said","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"quarantines may discourage health workers from traveling to West Africa","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"to help block the disease at its source .","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"`` If you put everyone in one basket , even people","depth":13},{"id":27,"text":"who are clearly no threat ,","depth":13},{"id":28,"text":"then we have the problem of the disincentive of people","depth":13},{"id":29,"text":"that we need , ''","depth":13},{"id":30,"text":"Fauci said on ABC 's This Week .","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"`` Let 's not forget","depth":12},{"id":32,"text":"the best way","depth":14},{"id":33,"text":"to stop this epidemic","depth":15},{"id":34,"text":"and protect America","depth":15},{"id":35,"text":"is to stop it in Africa ,","depth":13},{"id":36,"text":"and you can really help stopping it in Africa","depth":12},{"id":37,"text":"if we have our people , our heroes , the health care workers ,","depth":13},{"id":38,"text":"go there","depth":14},{"id":39,"text":"and help us to protect America . ''","depth":14},{"id":40,"text":"Power ,","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"who is traveling in West Africa ,","depth":12},{"id":42,"text":"told NBC News","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"that quarantine plans in New York , New Jersey and Illinois are `` haphazard and not well thought out , ''","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"and could discourage health workers from going to West Africa in the first place .","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"`` We can not take measures here","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"that are going to impact our ability","depth":13},{"id":47,"text":"to flood the zone , ''","depth":13},{"id":48,"text":"Power said .","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"`` We have to find the right balance","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"between addressing the legitimate fears","depth":13},{"id":51,"text":"that people have","depth":13},{"id":52,"text":"and encouraging and incentivizing these heroes . ''","depth":12},{"id":53,"text":"Officials in New Jersey , New York and Illinois ,","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"who acted in the wake of a new Ebola case in New York ,","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"said","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"they can not rely on people to quarantine themselves .","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"`` I do n't think","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"when you 're dealing with something as serious as this","depth":13},{"id":59,"text":"you can count on a voluntary system , ''","depth":13},{"id":60,"text":"said New Jersey Gov . Chris Christie , a Republican ,","depth":12},{"id":61,"text":"speaking on Fox News Sunday .","depth":12},{"id":62,"text":"`` This is the government 's job . ''","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"He added :","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"`` I think","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"this is a policy","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"that will become a national policy sooner or later . ''","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"Florida Gov . Rick Scott , a Republican","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"locked in a tough battle for re-election next month ,","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"on Saturday ordered twice daily monitoring for 21 days for anyone","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"returning from places","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"affected by Ebola .","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"New York Gov . Andrew Cuomo , a Democrat , defended the quarantine policy Sunday in a radio interview .","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"But by Sunday evening , Cuomo had loosened the quarantine restrictions .","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"He said","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"health care workers can be quarantined at home , receive twice-daily monitoring from medical professionals ,","depth":13},{"id":76,"text":"and the state will also pay for any lost compensation .","depth":13},{"id":77,"text":"On Friday , Cuomo had said","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"the workers would be held in a government-regulated facility .","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"In New Jersey , a nurse with Doctors Without Borders","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"who worked with Ebola patients in Sierra Leone","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"became the first person","depth":13},{"id":82,"text":"to be quarantined under the new regulations","depth":13},{"id":83,"text":"when she arrived at Newark Liberty International Airport on Friday .","depth":12},{"id":84,"text":"The nurse , Kaci Hickox , criticized the way","depth":12},{"id":85,"text":"her case has been handled ,","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"raising concerns from humanitarian and human rights groups over unclear policies for the newly launched quarantine program .","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"Norman Siegel , Hickox 's attorney , told CNN","depth":12},{"id":88,"text":"he will go to court","depth":13},{"id":89,"text":"seeking a hearing ,","depth":13},{"id":90,"text":"saying","depth":12},{"id":91,"text":"her quarantine was based on fear .","depth":12},{"id":92,"text":"`` People are panicking ,","depth":12},{"id":93,"text":"and people are scared , ''","depth":12},{"id":94,"text":"he said .","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"Hickox said in a telephone interview with CNN","depth":12},{"id":96,"text":"that her confinement to an isolation tent at University Hospital in Newark hospital was `` inhumane '' and akin to being in prison .","depth":12},{"id":97,"text":"She said","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"she has no symptoms","depth":13},{"id":99,"text":"and tested negative for Ebola .","depth":13},{"id":100,"text":"`` This is an extreme","depth":13},{"id":101,"text":"that is really unacceptable ,","depth":13},{"id":102,"text":"and I feel","depth":13},{"id":103,"text":"like my basic human rights have been violated , ''","depth":13},{"id":104,"text":"Hickox said on CNN 's `` State of the Union . ''","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"Hickox wrote a first-person account for the Dallas Morning News ,","depth":12},{"id":106,"text":"which was posted on the paper 's website Saturday .","depth":12},{"id":107,"text":"`` This is not a situation","depth":15},{"id":108,"text":"I would wish on anyone ,","depth":15},{"id":109,"text":"and I am scared for those","depth":15},{"id":110,"text":"who will follow me , ''","depth":15},{"id":111,"text":"Hickox wrote of her quarantine .","depth":13},{"id":112,"text":"`` I am scared about how health care workers will be treated at airports","depth":15},{"id":113,"text":"when they declare","depth":16},{"id":114,"text":"that they have been fighting Ebola in West Africa .","depth":16},{"id":115,"text":"I am scared","depth":15},{"id":116,"text":"that , like me , they will arrive","depth":16},{"id":117,"text":"and see a frenzy of disorganization , fear and , most frightening , quarantine . ...","depth":16},{"id":118,"text":"The U.S. must treat returning health care workers with dignity and humanity . ''","depth":13},{"id":119,"text":"New York Mayor Bill de Blasio said","depth":11},{"id":120,"text":"Hickox had been treated with disrespect . ''","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"The quarantine measures were announced","depth":7},{"id":122,"text":"after New York physician Craig Spencer was hospitalized and tested positive for Ebola last Thursday ,","depth":9},{"id":123,"text":"following his return","depth":10},{"id":124,"text":"from treating patients in Guinea with Doctors Without Borders .","depth":10},{"id":125,"text":"In the week after his return","depth":10},{"id":126,"text":"but before becoming symptomatic","depth":10},{"id":127,"text":"he rode the subway ,","depth":10},{"id":128,"text":"went bowling","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"and ate at a restaurant .","depth":11},{"id":130,"text":"De Blasio visited the treatment ward at Bellevue Hospital","depth":8},{"id":131,"text":"and spoke with Spencer .","depth":8},{"id":132,"text":"At a news conference later he said","depth":9},{"id":133,"text":"health workers should be regarded as heroes","depth":10},{"id":134,"text":"and likened them to U.S. Marines on the front-lines of danger .","depth":10},{"id":135,"text":"`` They are the first responders","depth":10},{"id":136,"text":"and they are doing an absolutely extraordinary job , ''","depth":10},{"id":137,"text":"he said .","depth":9},{"id":138,"text":"Hospital officials said on Saturday","depth":6},{"id":139,"text":"that Spencer was experiencing gastrointestinal symptoms","depth":7},{"id":140,"text":"and `` entering the next phase of his illness . ''","depth":7},{"id":141,"text":"Republican members of Congress have called on the Obama administration to enact more travel restrictions into and out of West Africa .","depth":3},{"id":142,"text":"Rep. Darrell Issa , R-Calif. , chairman of the House Oversight and Government Reform Committee , told CNN 's State of the Union","depth":5},{"id":143,"text":"that state officials are taking action in the absence of federal leadership .","depth":5},{"id":144,"text":"`` Governors of both parties are reacting","depth":6},{"id":145,"text":"because there is n't a trust in the leadership of this administration , ''","depth":6},{"id":146,"text":"Issa said .","depth":5},{"id":147,"text":"Contributing :","depth":2},{"id":148,"text":"William M. Welch in Los Angeles ; The Associated Press","depth":2}],"relations":[{"parent":297,"left":295,"right":296,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":295,"left":289,"right":294,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":289,"left":168,"right":288,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":168,"left":163,"right":167,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":163,"left":156,"right":162,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":156,"left":152,"right":155,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":152,"left":151,"right":3,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":151,"left":0,"right":150,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":150,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":155,"left":4,"right":154,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":154,"left":5,"right":153,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":153,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":162,"left":8,"right":161,"relation":"adv